The paper deals with the design of a beamformer for a secondary transmitter to improve the secrecy of the primary network in the presence of an eavesdropper. This involves optimizing the use of spectral resources through cooperation between primary and secondary users. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their information-carrying capacities. The paper also deals with physical layer security, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of multiple antennas for beamforming involves signal processing, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves system-level design and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves numerical simulations, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
